      "@type": "owl:DatatypeProperty",
      "rdfs:comment": [
        "NOTE: Values of predicates with different precisions can be compared since they are all formally xsd:datetimes.",
        "NOTE: This property is neutral along two dimensions: precision (e.g., day, second, millisecond) and actual vs. planned. As such, it will generally not be asserted directly except in special cases (e.g., for time intervals).",
        "DEFINITION: The date and time that something ends."
      ],
